A concurrent resolution directing the Clerk of the House of Representatives to make a correction in the enrollment of H.R. 5325.

vote.text: Submitted in the Senate, considered, and agreed to without amendment by Unanimous Consent.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.
Mr. Rogers (KY) asked unanimous consent to take from the Speaker's table and consider.

reference.label: text of measure as received in House

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary:
(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)
Directs the Clerk of the House of Representatives to make a correction in the enrollment of H.R. 5325 to change the title to read "Making continuing appropriations for fiscal year 2017, and for other purposes."
